		<div id="comment_body_64751372">The 0.5V IS the integrated potential over a 300km thick ionosphere.  It is a very small potential that has a very large effect.  Atmospheric scientists knew this field was present because it explains the disparity between air density based just on mass of atmospheric gases and gravity versus what is observed.  (We also know that the disparity in thermal energy induced velocities of electrons and ions enables this "puffing").</div>
